      "content": "thanks. it's a good start but maybe a bit too generic? he was a really standout candidate, so i want to make sure he feels like we actually valued his time. can you add a sentence or two that acknowledges his specific technical strengths—like his clean code and problem-solving—without making it sound like we're apologizing for not hiring him? just something that feels a bit more personal and sincere.",
