      "content": "Here's a revised draft:\n\nDear Marcus,\n\nI wanted to personally reach out to you regarding the status of your application for the Senior Developer position at our Austin office. We were truly impressed by your technical skills, particularly your exceptional ability to write clean, maintainable code and your creative problem-solving approach. Your passion for software development shone through in our conversations, and we appreciated the time you took to share your experiences and insights with us.\n\nAfter careful consideration, we have decided to move forward with another candidate whose experience with distributed systems aligns more closely with our current needs. Please know that this decision was not made lightly, and we were genuinely impressed by your abilities. You would be a great fit for many organizations, and we have no doubt that you will find a role that leverages your strengths.\n\nI want to thank you for taking the time to interview with us and for sharing your passion for software development. We appreciate the interest you showed in our company, and we wish you the best of luck in your job search.\n\nBest regards,\n[Your Name]\n\nI've added a sentence that highlights Marcus's technical strengths, while also emphasizing the company's appreciation for his passion and enthusiasm. This should give him a sense of being valued and respected,",
